ggle_list%22%3A%22%5Bhavnor_simple_lists%5D%5Bhavnor_simple_list%20list_text%3D%5C%22Distribution%20Strategy%5C%22%5D%5Bhavnor_simple_list%20list_text%3D%5C%22New%20Product%20Development%5C%22%5D%5Bhavnor_simple_list%20list_text%3D%5C%22Commercialization%5C%22%5D%5B%2Fhavnor_simple_lists%5D%22%7D%5D" icon_color="#4285f4" title_weight="500" tgl_btn_bg_color="rgba(66,133,244,0.23)"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544072479424{padding-top: 6% !important;}"][vc_column][havnor_section_title title_align="center" title_text="You Can Ask Questions" content_text="Questions are focus on our clients' most critical issues and opportunities." title_size="36px" title_fw="500"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544072486934{padding-bottom: 9% !important;}"][vc_column offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-6"][vc_accordion accordion_style="style-one"][vc_accordion_tab title="Where should I incorporate my business?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]The standard answer to this is Delaware because of its well developed corporate law. My answer is that it should be the state where the business is located, as this will save you some fees and complexities. You can always reincorporate later in Delaware.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How much should I capitalize my business?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]As much as you can reasonably afford, and in an amount to at least carry you for 6-9 months with no income. What you will find is that it always takes you longer to get revenues, and that you will experience more expenses than you anticipated.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How much dilution in share ownership business?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Whatever amount gets you funded. Don’t try to over-optimize on ownership. Get cash to grow your business and make your investors happy as well.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How big should a stock option for employees?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]15-20%. Standard vesting for options is 4 years, with a one year “cliff vesting” and monthly vesting after that. “Cliff vesting” in this context means the employee must be employed by the company for a minimum of one year before the employee earns any of the options.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How can I get a venture capitalist to pay?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Any of the following:
Get a ton of traction in the marketplace
Have meaningful growing revenues
Have a world-class management team
Have truly innovative technology with a big market opportunity
Get a personal introduction to one of the VC firm partners from a respected colleague[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How can I come up with name for my business?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]This is difficult. First brainstorm with a bunch of different names. Then do a Google search to see what is already taken, and that will eliminate 95% of your choices. Make it easy to spell. Make it interesting. Don’t pick a nonsensical name where people won’t have a clue as to what you do (with all due consideration to names like “Google,” “Yahoo,” and the like). Do a trademark/tradename search on the name. Then make sure you can get the domain name. [/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What are the biggest challenges in a business?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Ideas are a dime a dozen. It’s the actual implementation of an idea that is more important. If it’s truly unique, get a patent for it (see www.uspto.gov). You may get some protection through copyright, trade secret programs, or NDA’s, but not a lot.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][vc_column offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-6"][vc_accordion accordion_style="style-one"][vc_accordion_tab title="How can I obtain the domain name I want?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Every good “.com” domain name is already taken. And I usually only recommend “.com” names. Ultimately, 99% of domain names are available to be bought -- you just have to be prepared to pay for the name. Do a “WHOIS Search” at www.networksolutions.com to find out the contact information for the owner of the domain name you are interested in, and offer to buy the name. Don’t be naive and offer $500 for a premium domain name. You will be ignored. Be willing to pay a fair amount for a good name.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Do I need a business plan?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]It’s useful to come up with a business plan to think through what you want to do for the development of the product or service, marketing, financial projections and more. Then get input from trusted business/finance advisors. But don’t go overboard with a 50-page business plan. In reality many start-ups have to deviate from their plan.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How to update premium plugins?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]In most cases, premium plugins bundled with the theme, do not get updates quickly. It depends on the theme update. But, in our all themes you can get updation of premium plugins by following simple steps.

Goto : Plugins &gt; Deactivate &amp; Delete that plugin.
Then Goto: Appearance &gt; Install Plugins.
Then: Install and Activate that plugin.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Where can I get money for my business?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Many books and articles have been written on this subject as well. Here is a summary of the most effective sources of capital:

Personal funds
Credit cards
Friends and family
Angel investors
Crowdsourcing sites such as Indiegogo.com and Kickstarter.com
Bank loans/SBA financings
Venture capitalists
Equipment loan financing[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Where can I get money for my business?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Many books and articles have been written on this subject as well. Here is a summary of the most effective sources of capital:

Personal funds
Credit cards
Friends and family
Angel investors
Crowdsourcing sites such as Indiegogo.com and Kickstarter.com
Bank loans/SBA financings
Venture capitalists
Equipment loan financing[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What permits, licenses, registrations for business?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]The update process is similar to the power process. In WordPress Dashboard, Cosgrove Options there is a section of Envato Account in this area you've to enter your Envato username and API key then Save the changes, You'll get our theme updation right into your WordPress Dashboard &gt; Updates.

Note: We hope you not edited anything inside of our theme core files. If you edit anything in our theme, this step will replace our original theme code, so you'll lose your past edited files in our theme. Editing theme core files are not recommended.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Need to worry about in hiring an employee?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Have you done a reference check?
Does the employee have relevant experience for the job?
Will the employee fit in with the company culture?
Do you have a good form of employment “at will” letter for the employee to sign (allowing you to terminate the employee for any reason if it’s not working out)?[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544775891234{background: #4285f4 url(https://victorthemes.com/themes/havnor/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dot-pattern.png?id=4636) !important;}"][vc_column css=".vc_custom_1539070052313{padding-top: 0px !important;}"][havnor_callout call_style="three" call_title="We thrive in the midst of tough, high-stakes challenges." btn_text="Connect Now" btn_link="#0" open_link="true" btn_text_color="#4285f4" btn_text_hover_color="#ffffff" btn_bg_color="#ffffff" btn_bg_hover_color="rgba(255,255,255,0.01)" btn_border_color="#ffffff" btn_border_hover_color="#ffffff" cta_bg_color="rgba(255,255,255,0.01)" title_size="34px" btn_text_size="13px"][/havnor_callout][/vc_column][/vc_row]
CONTENT;
    array_unshift($data, $template);
    return $data;
  }

